#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.35:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Dānavagga"
msgstr "4. Giving"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Dānūpapattisutta"
msgstr "35. Rebirth by Giving"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.35:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhimā, bhikkhave, dānūpapattiyo."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these eight rebirths by giving."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.2"
msgid "Katamā aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.35:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ "
"vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"First, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins such things as food, drink, "
"clothing, vehicles; garlands, fragrance, and makeup; and bed, house, and "
"lighting."

#. VAR: paccāsīsati → paccāsiṃsati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:1.4"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati."
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.5"
msgid ""
"So passati khattiyamahāsāle vā brāhmaṇamahāsāle vā gahapatimahāsāle vā "
"pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappite samaṅgībhūte paricārayamāne."
msgstr ""
"They see a well-to-do aristocrat or brahmin or householder amusing "
"themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It occurs to them:"

msgctxt "an8.35:1.7"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā "
"brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders!’"

msgctxt "an8.35:1.8"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that idea, stabilize it and develop it."

#. VAR: hīne vimuttaṃ → hīnedhimuttaṃ (s1-3, pts1) | vimuttanti vā vissaṭṭhaṃ (ṭīkāsaṃvaṇṇanā)
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:1.9"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"As they’ve settled for less and not developed further, their idea leads to "
"rebirth there."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.10"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā "
"gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of "
"well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.11"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa."
msgstr ""
"But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the "
"unethical."

msgctxt "an8.35:1.12"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (1)"
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.240"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an8.35:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ "
"pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ."
msgstr "Next, someone gives to ascetics or brahmins …"

msgctxt "an8.35:2.2"
msgid "So yaṃ deti taṃ paccāsīsati."
msgstr "Whatever they give, they expect something back."

msgctxt "an8.35:2.3"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

#. VAR: cātumahārājikā → cātummahārājikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.35:2.4"
msgid "‘cātumahārājikā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Gods of the Four Great Kings are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy.’"

msgctxt "an8.35:2.5"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It occurs to them:"

msgctxt "an8.35:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Gods of the Four Great Kings!’ …"

msgctxt "an8.35:2.7"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.35:2.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an8.35:2.9"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"Gods of the Four Great Kings."

msgctxt "an8.35:2.10"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa."
msgstr ""
"But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the "
"unethical."

msgctxt "an8.35:2.11"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (2)"
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.35:3.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ "
