msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It occurs to them:"

msgctxt "an8.35:3.10"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the Gods Who Control the Creations of Others!’"

msgctxt "an8.35:3.11"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr "They settle on that idea, stabilize it and develop it."

msgctxt "an8.35:3.12"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ hīne vimuttaṃ, uttari abhāvitaṃ, tatrūpapattiyā saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"As they’ve settled for less and not developed further, their idea leads to "
"rebirth there."

msgctxt "an8.35:3.13"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā paranimmitavasavattīnaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"Gods Who Control the Creations of Others."

msgctxt "an8.35:3.14"
msgid "Tañca kho sīlavato vadāmi, no dussīlassa."
msgstr ""
"But I say that this is only for those of ethical conduct, not for the "
"unethical."

msgctxt "an8.35:3.15"
msgid "Ijjhati, bhikkhave, sīlavato cetopaṇidhi visuddhattā. (3–7.)"
msgstr "The heart’s wish of an ethical person succeeds because of their purity."

#. </p><p>
